✅ 3. Measure Database Query Time (PostgreSQL)
Enter DB pod
Bash
kubectl exec -it <postgres-pod> -- psql -U <user> -d <db>
Find currently running slow queries
SQL
SELECT pid,
       now() - query_start AS duration,
       query
FROM pg_stat_activity
WHERE state='active'
ORDER BY duration DESC;
Enable slow query logging (runtime — no restart)
SQL
ALTER SYSTEM SET log_min_duration_statement = 100;
SELECT pg_reload_conf();
Logs queries taking >100ms.
Check slow queries
Inside pod:
Bash
kubectl logs <postgres-pod> | grep duration
Example output:

duration: 532 ms execute select ...
👉 This is pure DB time.
